Steps to Repair the Table: 

Open MySQL Command Line:

On your terminal, log into MySQL with your credentials.

# mysql -u database username -p

Enter your password when prompted.

Select Your Database:

# USE Database_name;

Repair the Table:
	
Run the repair command on the table. Eg :: wp_options
	
# REPAIR TABLE wp_options;

You can verify if the table is repaired by rerunning the CHECK TABLE command.

# CHECK TABLE wp_options;
